v0.4.1 : 18 / 12 / 2002
- fully functionnal under internet explorer (thx ben)
- fixed lotta minor bugs about javascript code
- removed events and firstjeudis information (obsolete as date related)
- fixed some undone translations
- added a 'back to full view' button under the reference map
- added icons to access directly to requets
- fixed security : maximum image size was not controlled (thx pascal)
- fixed : keeping now the zoom level when click on a city on list

v0.4 : 23 / 10 / 2002
- first public release
- added a spanish translation by Diego Duchowney
- found translators for breitz and corsica
- fixed lotta minor bugs about navigation and links
- built a draft data display
- added feature that enable user input on the map by a click.
- added multilingual capability. French, english and spanish 
are the closest goals (we need sample maps to use with those
languages).
- General mysql work for data search

v0.3 : 10 / 2002
First public release of source code at berlios.de
bundled with a free set of maps of French country.
http://localis.org 

v0.2 : 06 / 2002
First public version used by Medias-Cite.org
visible at http://localis.medias-cite.org
(version used and patched by Gerald Elbaze, 
named "Localis Medias-Cité v1.0")

v0.1 : 04 / 2002
First working version worked with Medias-Cite.org
with raster maps of aquitaine and cities localisation.
